Interface EvaluationObserver

All Known Implementing Classes:
ConsoleLoggerObserver
public interface EvaluationObserver
Defines a contract for observing the evaluation process of a class.

Implementations of this interface receive notifications at key stages of the evaluation process for a given class, providing hooks for custom behaviors during those events.

  • Method Details

    • onEvaluationStart

      void onEvaluationStart(String className)
      Notifies the observer that the evaluation process has started for the specified class.

      This method is called when the evaluation process begins. Implementations can use this notification to initialize resources or log the start of the evaluation.

      Parameters:
      className - the fully qualified name of the class being evaluated. This value is guaranteed to be non-null and non-empty.

    • onEvaluationComplete

      void onEvaluationComplete(String className)
      Notifies the observer that the evaluation process has completed for the specified class.

      This method is called once the evaluation process has finished. Implementations can use this notification to finalize resources, log results, or trigger subsequent actions.

      Parameters:
      className - the fully qualified name of the class whose evaluation has completed. This value is guaranteed to be non-null and non-empty.
